cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language modeling and natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach for training neural language models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of language models using syntactic information.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural language models.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a novel approach for applying language models to unparsed text using sequential Monte Carlo sampling, which could have applications in computer vision.
